without a glass in her hand.

00:12:47.401 --> 00:12:48.737 position:27% line:89% align:start
So, is Lenya...?

00:12:49.136 --> 00:12:51.506 position:10% line:89% align:start
Short for Letana Andreanova.

00:12:52.707 --> 00:12:54.676 position:27% line:83% align:start
It's the nickname
my mama went by.

00:12:55.409 --> 00:12:59.079 position:7% line:83% align:start
I knew Lenya years ago when we
were barely more than children.

00:12:59.213 --> 00:13:00.981 position:10% line:83% align:start
She and I spent a lot of time
together

00:13:01.115 --> 00:13:02.651 position:35% line:83% align:start
growing up
at this very orphanage.

00:13:02.783 --> 00:13:05.819 position:30% line:83% align:start
So you grew up
at the orphanage, too, Natalia?

00:13:06.086 --> 00:13:07.522 position:24% line:89% align:start
You got that right.

00:13:07.656 --> 00:13:10.457 position:16% line:83% align:start
But actually, in my case,
I didn't spend much time away.

00:13:10.592 --> 00:13:11.626 position:35% line:89% align:start
[laughing]

00:13:12.793 --> 00:13:15.462 position:10% line:83% align:start
[NATALIA] Without any family
reputation to work off of,

00:13:15.597 --> 00:13:17.097 position:19% line:89% align:start
I had a difficult time

00:13:17.231 --> 00:13:19.466 position:10% line:83% align:start
finding anyone who would dare
to trust me with a job.

00:13:19.833 --> 00:13:22.970 position:7% line:83% align:start
And I didn't have the privilege
of any schooling either.

00:13:24.405 --> 00:13:27.841 position:16% line:83% align:start
So I decided to return to
the coop that I had just flown.

00:13:28.375 --> 00:13:30.779 position:24% line:83% align:start
